<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><access>package_private</access><active>true</active><api_name>x_126749_aws_sc.AbstractAwsAjaxProcessor</api_name><client_callable>false</client_callable><description/><name>AbstractAwsAjaxProcessor</name><script><![CDATA[/**
 * Functions for AJAX Processors.
 */
var AbstractAwsAjaxProcessor = /** @class */ (function (_super) {
    Polyfill.__extends(AbstractAwsAjaxProcessor, _super);
    function AbstractAwsAjaxProcessor() {
        return _super !== null && _super.apply(this, arguments) || this;
    }
    AbstractAwsAjaxProcessor.prototype._applyWith = function (suppliers, callback) {
        var result;
        try {
            var args = [];
            for (var i = 0, l = suppliers.length; i < l; i++) {
                var v = suppliers[i].get(this);
                if (v instanceof Error) {
                    return this._errorResponse(v.message);
                }
                else {
                    args.push(v);
                }
            }
            result = callback.apply(this, args);
        }
        catch (e) {
            var msg = (e.message ? e.message : e.toString());
            gs.warn("Unhandled error calling " + callback.name + ": " + msg);
            return this._errorResponse("Unhandled error: " + msg);
        }
        if (typeof result === 'string') {
            return result;
        }
        else if (!result) {
            result = 'ok';
        }
        return this._response(JSON.stringify(result));
    };
    AbstractAwsAjaxProcessor.prototype._getAllUserRoles = function (productSysId) {
        return ProductUserCriteria.availableIdentities(gs.getUserID(), productSysId);
    };
    AbstractAwsAjaxProcessor.prototype._getProduct = function (id) {
        var gr = new GlideRecord('x_126749_aws_sc_product');
        return gr.get(id) ? gr : null;
    };
    AbstractAwsAjaxProcessor.prototype._getProductFromProvisioned = function (ppGR) {
        var event = new GlideRecord('x_126749_aws_sc_pp_event');
        event.addQuery('awsproduct', ppGR.sys_id);
        event.setLimit(1);
        event.query();
        if (!event.next()) {
            return null;
        }
        var product = new GlideRecord('x_126749_aws_sc_product');
        product.addQuery('awsregion', ppGR.awsregion.toString());
        product.addQuery('awsproductid', event.awsproductid.toString());
        product.query();
        if (!product.next()) {
            return null;
        }
        return product;
    };
    AbstractAwsAjaxProcessor.prototype._getServiceCatalog = function (region, credential) {
        return new AwsServiceCatalog(region, credential);
    };
    AbstractAwsAjaxProcessor.prototype._getCloudFormation = function (region, credential) {
        return new AwsCloudFormation(region, credential);
    };
    AbstractAwsAjaxProcessor.prototype._isEmpty = function (param) {
        return param.trim() === "";
    };
    AbstractAwsAjaxProcessor.prototype._isMissing = function (param) {
        return param === undefined || param === null;
    };

        return this._isMissing(param) || this._isEmpty(param);
    };
    AbstractAwsAjaxProcessor.prototype._missingParameter = function (param) {
        return this._errorResponse('Missing parameter: ' + param);
    };
    AbstractAwsAjaxProcessor.prototype._errorResponse = function (msg, result) {
        var obj = '{"success": false, "message": ' + JSON.stringify(msg);

            }
            obj += ', "result": ' + result;
        }
        obj += '}';
        return obj;
    };
    AbstractAwsAjaxProcessor.prototype._response = function (body) {
        if (typeof body === 'object') {
            body = JSON.stringify(body);
        }
        return '{"success": true, "result": ' + body + '}';

sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_ui_page"><sys_ui_page action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><category>general</category><client_script/><description/><direct>false</direct><endpoint>x_126749_aws_sc_execute_self_service_action.do</endpoint><html><![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?>
<j:jelly trim="false" xmlns:j="jelly:core" xmlns:g="glide" xmlns:j2="null" xmlns:g2="null">
    <g:requires name="angular_includes_1.4.jsx"/>
    <g:requires name="x_126749_aws_sc.awsComponents.jsdbx"/>
    <g:requires name="x_126749_aws_sc.productCatalog.jsdbx"/>
    <head>
        <title>Execute Self-Service Action</title>
    </head>
    <body ng-app="productCatalog">

    <g:evaluate object="true">
        // Get session token. Required so we can use $http in Service Portal. See
        // https://community.servicenow.com/community?id=community_blog&sys_id=bebc6e25dbd0dbc01dcaf3231f961928
        // Note ServiceNow documentation says that GlideSystem's getSessionToken()
        // method "is no longer available. Instead, use gs.getSession().getSessionToken()."
        // Experimentally on Istanbul this is not true on this page, only in server scripts.
        var session = gs.getSession();
        var token;
        gs.info('session found ' + session);
        var token = session.getSessionToken();
        if (!token) {
            try {
                token = gs.getSessionToken();
            } catch (err) {
                gs.debug('Fallback to GlideSession.getSessionToken failed');
            }
        }
    </g:evaluate>

    <header></header>
    <main>
        <execute-self-service-action-ui user-token="$[token]"></execute-self-service-action-ui>
    </main>
    <footer></footer>
    </body>
</j:jelly>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><access>package_private</access><active>true</active><api_name>x_126749_aws_sc.AjaxParameterSupplier</api_name><client_callable>false</client_callable><description/><name>AjaxParameterSupplier</name><script><![CDATA[/**
 * @class AjaxParameterSupplier
 * @classdesc
 * AjaxParameterSupplier handles the transformation of AJAX Processors
 * request parameters into interesting objects.
 * @param name {string} The name of a request parameter.
 * @param required {boolean=} Whether the parameter is strictly required, default true.
 * @param fns {Array<Function>} Optional array of functions to call in order.
 */
var AjaxParameterSupplier = /** @class */ (function () {
    function AjaxParameterSupplier(name, required, fns) {
        this.type = 'AjaxParameterSupplier';
        this._argName = name;
        this._required = required !== false;
        this._fns = fns || [];
    }
    AjaxParameterSupplier.prototype.getArgument = function () {
        return this._argName;
    };
    AjaxParameterSupplier.prototype.get = function (ajaxProcessor) {
        var current = ajaxProcessor.getParameter(this._argName);
        if (this._required && ajaxProcessor._isMissingOrEmpty(current)) {
            return new Error(this._argName + ": missing");
        }
        if (current) {
            for (var i = 0, l = this._fns.length; i < l; i++) {
                current = this._fns[i].call(this, current);
                if (current instanceof Error) {
                    break;
                }
            }
        }
        return current;
    };
    AjaxParameterSupplier.prototype._instanceCalling = function (fn) {
        var fns = this._fns.slice();
        fns.push(fn);
        return new AjaxParameterSupplier(this._argName, this._required, fns);
    };
    AjaxParameterSupplier.prototype.gr = function (table) {
        var an = this._argName;
        return this._instanceCalling(function (sysId) {
            var g = new GlideRecord(table);
            if (!g.get(sysId)) {
                return new Error(an + ": no such record " + sysId);
            }
            return g;
        });
    };
    AjaxParameterSupplier.prototype.notNil = function (col) {
        var an = this._argName;
        return this._instanceCalling(function (gr) {
            if (gr[col].nil()) {
                return new Error(an + ": nil value for " + col);
            }
            return gr;
        });
    };
    AjaxParameterSupplier.prototype.fromJSON = function () {
        var an = this._argName;
        return this._instanceCalling(function (s) {
            try {
                return JSON.parse(s);
            }
            catch (e) {
                var m = an + ": error parsing JSON: " + (e.message ? e.message : e.toString());
                return new Error(m);
            }
        });
    };
    AjaxParameterSupplier.prototype.then = function (fn) {
        return this._instanceCalling(fn);
    };
    AjaxParameterSupplier.required = function (name) {
        return new AjaxParameterSupplier(name, true);
    };
    AjaxParameterSupplier.optional = function (name) {
        return new AjaxParameterSupplier(name, false);
    };
    return AjaxParameterSupplier;
}());
]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_include</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>admin</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2018-10-11 14:05:47</sys_created_on><sys_id>aba4641edb892300e9727d9ebf961925</sys_id><sys_mod_count>4</sys_mod_count><sys_name>AjaxParameterSupplier</sys_name><sys_package display_value="AWS Service Catalog - 2.0.2" source="x_126749_aws_sc">f0b117a3db32320093a7d7a0cf961912</sys_package><sys_policy>read</sys_policy><sys_scope display_value="AWS Service Catalog - 2.0.2">f0b117a3db32320093a7d7a0cf961912</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_include_aba4641edb892300e9727d9ebf961925</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>admin</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2019-03-12 11:48:13</sys_updated_on></sys_script_include></record_update>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><access>package_private</access><active>true</active><api_name>x_126749_aws_sc.ProvisionedProductPlan</api_name><client_callable>false</client_callable><description/><name>ProvisionedProductPlan</name><script><![CDATA[var ProvisionedProductPlan = /** @class */ (function () {
    function ProvisionedProductPlan(plan, pp) {

            pp.awsid = ppId;
            pp.awsstatus = "PLAN_IN_PROGRESS";

    /**

     * @param provisionedProduct The provisioned product the plan is destined for

     */

        var credentialSupplier = provisionedProduct.getCredentialSupplier();
        if (!credentialSupplier.isValid()) {

    };
    ProvisionedProductPlan.prototype.deletePlan = function () {
        var credentialSupplier = this.pp.getCredentialSupplier();
        if (!credentialSupplier.isValid()) {
            return Util.failure('Authentication failure');
        }

    ProvisionedProductPlan.prototype.describe = function (sync) {

        var description = {};

            ProductId: this.gr.awsproductid.toString(),
            PlanName: this.gr.awsplanname.toString(),
            PlanId: this.gr.awsplanid.toString(),
            ProvisionProductId: this.gr.awsprovisionproductid.toString(),
            ProvisionProductName: this.gr.awsprovisionproductname.toString(),
            PlanType: this.gr.awsplantype.toString(),
            ProvisioningArtifactId: this.gr.awsprovisioningartifactid.toString(),
            Status: this.gr.awsstatus.toString(),

        };

        description.LastSyncTime = (!this.gr.awslastsynctime.nil() ? new GlideDateTime(this.gr.awslastsynctime).getNumericValue() : '');
        if (this.getStatus() !== "CREATE_IN_PROGRESS") {

            rc.addQuery('awsplan', this.gr.sys_id);
            rc.query();

                var scope = void 0;

                    scope = JSON.parse(rc.awsscope.toString());

            rcExists.addQuery('awsplan', this.gr.sys_id);
            rcExists.setLimit(1);
            rcExists.query();

                var allChanges = response.collectAll();
                if (!allChanges.success) {
                    return this.updateSyncStatus(2 /* ERROR */);
                }

    };
    ProvisionedProductPlan.prototype.execute = function (token) {
        var cred = this.pp.getCredentialSupplier();
        if (!cred.isValid()) {
            return Util.failure("Authentication failure");
        }
        gs.debug("Executing provisioned product plan " + this.getPlanId() + " on " + this.pp.getName());
        var sc = this.pp._getServiceCatalog(this.pp.getRegion(), cred);
        var response = sc.executeProvisionedProductPlan(this.getPlanId(), token), body = response.deserialize();
        if (!response.haveError()) {
            this.pp.gr().awsstatus = "UNDER_CHANGE" /* UNDER_CHANGE */;
            this.pp.gr().awsproductstatus = 2 /* PROVISIONING */;
            this.gr.awsstatus = "EXECUTE_IN_PROGRESS";
            this.gr.update();
            return Util.success(body);
        }
        else {
            return Util.failure(Util.explainError(body), response.isRequestRetryable());
        }
    };
    /**
     * @return the ID of this plan in AWS.
     */
    ProvisionedProductPlan.prototype.getPlanId = function () {
        return this.gr.awsplanid.toString();
    };
    ProvisionedProductPlan.prototype.getProvisionedProduct = function () {
        return this.pp;
    };
    /**
     * @param sync {boolean}
     *      Synchronize the plan with AWS Service Catalog if it is currently
     *      CREATE_IN_PROGRESS or EXECUTE_IN_PROGRESS.
     * @return the status of this plan in AWS.
     */
    ProvisionedProductPlan.prototype.getStatus = function (sync) {
        if ((typeof sync !== "undefined" && sync) && this.isInProgress()) {
            this.sync();
        }
        return this.gr.awsstatus.toString();
    };
    ProvisionedProductPlan.prototype.getSysId = function () {
        return this.gr.sys_id.toString();
    };
    /**
     * True if this plan is CREATE_IN_PROGRESS or EXECUTE_IN_PROGRESS.
     */
    ProvisionedProductPlan.prototype.isInProgress = function () {
        var status = this.gr.awsstatus.toString();
        return status === "CREATE_IN_PROGRESS" || status === "EXECUTE_IN_PROGRESS";
    };
    ProvisionedProductPlan.prototype.updateSyncStatus = function (status) {
        this.gr.awssyncstatus = status;
        this.gr.update();
    };

}());
]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_include</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>admin</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2019-03-12 11:48:59</sys_created_on><sys_id>1107b2cfdb0033006c85ab7dca961976</sys_id><sys_mod_count>15</sys_mod_count><sys_name>ProvisionedProductPlan</sys_name><sys_package display_value="AWS Service Catalog - 2.0.2" source="x_126749_aws_sc">f0b117a3db32320093a7d7a0cf961912</sys_package><sys_policy>read</sys_policy><sys_scope display_value="AWS Service Catalog - 2.0.2">f0b117a3db32320093a7d7a0cf961912</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_include_1107b2cfdb0033006c85ab7dca961976</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>admin</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2019-04-10 11:12:49</sys_updated_on></sys_script_include></record_update>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><access>package_private</access><active>true</active><api_name>x_126749_aws_sc.AwsService</api_name><client_callable>false</client_callable><description/><name>AwsService</name><script><![CDATA[/**
 * @class
 * @classdesc Make HTTP requests to AWS services.
 * @param service {String} The name of the AWS service
 * @param region {String} An AWS region, e.g. "us-west-1"
 * @param credential {Object} AWS account credentials.
 * @param credential.identity {String} An AWS access key.
 * @param credential.secret {String} An AWS secret access key.
 * @param credential.session {String=} Required if using temporary credentials.
 */
var AwsService = /** @class */ (function () {
    function AwsService(service, region, credential) {
        /**
         * Creating a system property with this name configures AwsService
         * to use the object named by the property to make HTTP requests.
         * @type {string}
         */
        this.httpRequesterSysProp = 'x_126749_aws_sc.httpRequester';
        this.service = Util.assertExists(service, "service");
        this.host = this.service;
        if (region) {
            this.host += "." + region;
        }
        this.host += ".amazonaws.com";
        this.endpoint = "https://" + this.host;
        this.region = region ? region : "us-east-1";
        if (credential && (this.isCredentialSupplier(credential) || (credential.identity && credential.secret))) {
            this.credential = credential;
            this.requester = this.loadRequester();
            this._requestCount = 0;
        }
        else {
            throw new Error("Invalid credential: object must be a supplier or have identity and secret properties");
        }
    }
    AwsService.prototype.isCredentialSupplier = function (obj) {
        return typeof obj["get"] === "function";
    };
    /** @return string the time in format yyyymmddThhmmssZ */
    AwsService.prototype.iso8601 = function () {
        // "2017-05-15T16:44:55.288Z" --> 20170515T164455Z
        var d = new Date().toISOString();
        d = d.replace(/[-:]/g, '');
        // strip milliseconds.
        d = d.replace(/\.\d\d\dZ/, 'Z');
        return d;
    };
    AwsService.prototype.loadRequester = function () {
        var sysProp = gs.getProperty(this.httpRequesterSysProp);
        if (sysProp) {
            var o = Util.getObjectWithName(sysProp);
            if (!o) {
                throw new Error("Value configured for system property " + this.httpRequesterSysProp +
                    " could not be loaded: " + sysProp);
            }
            return o;
        }
        return sn_ws.RESTMessageV2;
    };
    AwsService.prototype.agent = function () {
        var instanceId = gs.getProperty("instance_id"), userId = gs.getUserID();
        return C.name + "/" + C.version + "/" + instanceId + (userId ? "/" + userId : "");
    };
    /**
     * Send an HTTP POST to the service.
     * @param action {String}
     * @param payload {(String|Object)}
     * @param additionalHeaders {Object}
     * @param queryParameters {Object=}
     * @returns {sn_ws.RESTResponseV2}
     * @throws Propagates errors thrown by credential suppliers.
     * @memberof! AwsService#
     * @alias _post
     * @private
     */
    AwsService.prototype._post = function (action, payload, additionalHeaders, queryParameters) {
        if (!payload) {
            payload = "";
        }
        else if (typeof payload === 'object') {
            payload = JSON.stringify(payload);
        }
        var request = new this.requester;
        request.setEndpoint(this.endpoint);
        request.setHttpMethod("POST");
        request.setRequestBody(payload);
        var isoDate = this.iso8601();
        var headers = {
            "Content-Length": payload.length,
            "Host": this.host,
            "X-Amz-Date": isoDate,
            "User-Agent": this.agent()
        };
        headers = Object.extend(headers, additionalHeaders);
        var requestCredential = this.credential;
        if (this.isCredentialSupplier(this.credential)) {
            requestCredential = requestCredential.get();
        }
        if (!requestCredential.identity || !requestCredential.secret) {
            throw new Error("Credential must have identity and secret properties");
        }
        if (requestCredential.session) {
            headers["X-Amz-Security-Token"] = requestCredential.session;
        }
        var signer = new AwsSignature(this.service, this.region, requestCredential, isoDate);
        headers["Authorization"] = signer.signV4("POST", headers, "/", queryParameters, payload);
        for (var h in headers) {
            if (headers.hasOwnProperty(h)) {
                request.setRequestHeader(h, headers[h]);
            }
        }
        var startTime = new GlideDateTime();
        var response = request.execute();
        var duration = new GlideDateTime().getNumericValue() - startTime.getNumericValue();

sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sysauto_script"><sysauto_script action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>true</active><condition/><conditional>false</conditional><name>Sync all Provisioned AWS Service Catalog Products</name><run_as/><run_as_tz/><run_dayofmonth>1</run_dayofmonth><run_dayofweek>1</run_dayofweek><run_period>1970-01-01 00:05:00</run_period><run_start>2017-10-17 17:35:09</run_start><run_time>1970-01-01 08:00:00</run_time><run_type>periodically</run_type><script><![CDATA[(function () {

    function syncOne(product) {
        new ProvisionedProduct(product, AwsCredentials).sync();
    }

    function syncAll() {
        var gr = new GlideRecord('x_126749_aws_sc_cmdb_ci_pp');
        var cond = gr.addQuery('awsstatus', '!=', 'AVAILABLE');
        cond.addOrCondition('awsproductstatus', '!=', ProvisionedProduct.Status.provisioned);
        gr.addQuery('awsproductstatus', '!=', ProvisionedProduct.Status.preProvisioning);
        gr.addQuery('awsproductstatus', '!=', ProvisionedProduct.Status.terminated);
        gr.query();
        while (gr.next()) {
            try {
                syncOne(gr);
            } catch (e) {
                gs.warn("Unexpected error syncing product " + gr.sys_id.toString() + ": " + e);
            }
        }
    }

    var startTime = new GlideDateTime().getNumericValue();
    syncAll();
    var completeTime = new GlideDateTime().getNumericValue();
    var seconds = (completeTime - startTime) / 1000.0;
    gs.info("Finished synchronizing Provisioned AWS Products in " + seconds + "s");

    TemporaryCredentialSupplier.cleanCache();
    gs.debug("Cleared temporary credentials");

})();
]]></script><sys_class_name>sysauto_script</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>admin</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2017-10-17 17:35:47</sys_created_on><sys_id>0ee1683edb3d0300a5d3ddd0cf9619c0</sys_id><sys_mod_count>11</sys_mod_count><sys_name>Sync all Provisioned AWS Service Catalog Products</sys_name><sys_package display_value="AWS Service Catalog - 2.0.2" source="x_126749_aws_sc">f0b117a3db32320093a7d7a0cf961912</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="AWS Service Catalog - 2.0.2">f0b117a3db32320093a7d7a0cf961912</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sysauto_script_0ee1683edb3d0300a5d3ddd0cf9619c0</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>admin</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2018-09-27 08:58:51</sys_updated_on><upgrade_safe>false</upgrade_safe></sysauto_script></record_update>

sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><access>package_private</access><active>true</active><api_name>x_126749_aws_sc.AwsSignature</api_name><client_callable>false</client_callable><description/><name>AwsSignature</name><script><![CDATA[var AwsSignature = /** @class */ (function () {
    /**
     * @param service The name of the AWS service
     * @param region e.g. "us-west-1"
     * @param credential Properties "identity" and "secret" are required, "session" is required if using temporary credentials.
     * @param isoDate The date in ISO 8601 format.
     */
    function AwsSignature(service, region, credential, isoDate) {
        this.crypto = CryptoJS;
        this.service = service;
        this.region = region ? region : "us-east-1";
        this.credential = credential;
        this.isoDate = isoDate;
        this.date = isoDate.substring(0, 8);
        this.credentialScope = this.date + "/" + this.region + "/" + this.service + "/aws4_request";
    }
    AwsSignature.prototype.signV4 = function (method, headers, path, query, payload) {
        var cr = this._createCanonicalRequest(method, headers, path, query, payload);
        var hashedCanonicalRequest = this._hashCanonicalRequest(cr.canonicalRequest);
        var stringToSign = this._createStringToSign(hashedCanonicalRequest);
        var signature = this._calculateSignature(stringToSign);
        return this._getAuthorizationHeader(cr.signedHeaders, signature);
    };
    AwsSignature.prototype._createCanonicalRequest = function (method, headers, path, query, payload) {
        // STAGE 1: create the canonical request
        /*
         CanonicalRequest =
         HTTPRequestMethod + '\n' +
         CanonicalURI + '\n' +
         CanonicalQueryString + '\n' +
         CanonicalHeaders + '\n' +
         SignedHeaders + '\n' +
         HexEncode(Hash(RequestPayload))
         */
        var canonicalRequest = method + "\n";
        canonicalRequest += encodeURI(this._normalize(path)) + "\n";
        if (query) {
            var queryPieces_1 = [];
            var encoder_1 = this._fixedEncodeURIComponent;
            Object.keys(query).sort().forEach(function (key, idx, arr) {
                var encKey = encoder_1(key);
                var val = query[key];
                function addParam(v) {
                    queryPieces_1.push(encKey + "=" + encoder_1(v));
                }
                if (Array.isArray(val)) {
                    // Slice to sort a copy of the value.
                    val.slice().sort().forEach(addParam, this);
                }
                else {
                    addParam(val);
                }
            }, this);
            canonicalRequest += queryPieces_1.join('&');
            canonicalRequest += "\n";
        }
        else {
            canonicalRequest += "\n";
        }
        var caseSortedHeaderKeys = Object.keys(headers)
            .sort(function (a, b) {
            var aL = a.toLowerCase();
            var bL = b.toLowerCase();
            return (aL < bL) ? -1 : ((bL < aL) ? 1 : 0);
        });
        var canonicalHeaders = caseSortedHeaderKeys.map(function (h) {
            // remove trailing spaces and sequential spaces within the rest of the string.
            var value = headers[h];
            if (value) {
                value = value.toString().trim().replace(/ +/g, ' ');
            }
            else {
                value = '';
            }
            return h.toLowerCase() + ":" + value + '\n';
        }).join('');
        var signedHeaders = caseSortedHeaderKeys.map(function (h) {
            return h.toLowerCase();
        }).join(';');
        canonicalRequest += canonicalHeaders + "\n";
        canonicalRequest += signedHeaders + "\n";
        canonicalRequest += this.crypto.SHA256(payload).toString();
        return {
            canonicalRequest: canonicalRequest,
            signedHeaders: signedHeaders
        };
    };
    AwsSignature.prototype._hashCanonicalRequest = function (canonicalRequest) {
        return this.crypto.SHA256(canonicalRequest).toString();
    };
    AwsSignature.prototype._createStringToSign = function (hashedCanonicalRequest) {
        // STAGE 2: create a string to sign
        /*
         StringToSign =
         Algorithm + \n +
         RequestDateTime + \n +
         CredentialScope + \n +
         HashedCanonicalRequest
         */
        var stringToSign = "";
        var algorithm = "AWS4-HMAC-SHA256";
        stringToSign += algorithm + "\n";
        stringToSign += this.isoDate + "\n";

    AwsSignature.prototype._calculateSignature = function (stringToSign) {

        // Derive the signing key.
        function getSignatureKey(Crypto, key, dateStamp, regionName, serviceName) {

            var kService = Crypto.HmacSHA256(serviceName, kRegion);
            var kSigning = Crypto.HmacSHA256("aws4_request", kService);
            return kSigning;
        }
        // Service Now errors if you assign the result of getSignatureKey to interim variable!
        return this.crypto.HmacSHA256(stringToSign, getSignatureKey(this.crypto, this.credential.secret, this.date, this.region, this.service)).toString();
    };
    AwsSignature.prototype._getAuthorizationHeader = function (signedHeaders, signature) {
        // STAGE 4: add an authorization header
        // Authorization: algorithm Credential=access key ID/credential scope, SignedHeaders=SignedHeaders, Signature=signature
        return "AWS4-HMAC-SHA256 Credential=" + this.credential.identity + "/" + this.credentialScope +

    /** Normalize a URL */
    AwsSignature.prototype._normalize = function (path) {

        // Uses an index into path rather than deletions from the start of the string.
        // Replace successive slashes with a single slash.

                index += 2;
            }
            else if (path.startsWith('../', index)) {
                index += 3;
            }
            // B
            else if (path.startsWith('/./', index)) {
                index += 2;
            }

                index += 2;
            }

                output = output.substring(0, output.lastIndexOf('/'));
            }

            }
            // E

                while (index < path.length && path.charAt(index) !== '/') {

    };

            return encodeURIComponent(s).replace(/[!'()*]/g, function (c) {

}());
AwsSignature.prototype.type = 'AwsSignature';
]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_include</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>admin</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2017-09-12 08:23:46</sys_created_on><sys_id>0af3921bdb010300cb04d421cf96198d</sys_id><sys_mod_count>6</sys_mod_count><sys_name>AwsSignature</sys_name><sys_package display_value="AWS Service Catalog - 2.0.2" source="x_126749_aws_sc">f0b117a3db32320093a7d7a0cf961912</sys_package><sys_policy>read</sys_policy><sys_scope display_value="AWS Service Catalog - 2.0.2">f0b117a3db32320093a7d7a0cf961912</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_include_0af3921bdb010300cb04d421cf96198d</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>admin</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2019-02-18 10:30:25</sys_updated_on></sys_script_include></record_update>

sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><access>package_private</access><active>true</active><api_name>x_126749_aws_sc.SynchronizeAccount</api_name><client_callable>false</client_callable><description/><name>SynchronizeAccount</name><script><![CDATA[var SynchronizeAccount = /** @class */ (function () {
    function SynchronizeAccount() {
        this.type = 'SynchronizeAccount';
        this._resetPortfolioCache();
    }
    /** Check that the instance is configured suitably to synchronise AWS Service Catalog. */
    SynchronizeAccount.prototype.validateInstance = function () {
        var skipPrefix = "Skipping AWS Service Catalog account synchronization: ";
        // Check the APIs are usable since some need plugins to be activated.
        try {
            new sn_uc.UserCriteria();
        }
        catch (e) {
            gs.error(skipPrefix + "cannot create sn_uc.UserCriteria. Check plugin " +
                "com.glideapp.user_criteria.scoped.api is enabled. Error: " + e.message);
            return false;
        }
        try {
            new sn_sc.CatalogItemVariableSetM2M();
        }
        catch (e) {
            gs.error(skipPrefix + "cannot create sn_sc.CatalogItemVariableSetM2M. Error: " + e.message);
            return false;
        }
        // Check the provisioning workflow exists.
        try {
            this._getProvisioningWorkflow();
        }
        catch (e) {
            gs.error(skipPrefix + "cannot load provisioning workflow: " + e.message);
            return false;
        }
        this.createPortfolioSubcategories =
            Util.tableActionEnabled("sc_category", true, true, true, true) &&
                Util.tableActionEnabled("sc_cat_item_category", true, true, true, true);
        if (!this.createPortfolioSubcategories) {
            gs.warn("Synchronization job will skip the creation of portfolio sub-categories because sc_category and/or " +
                "sc_cat_item_category are misconfigured. Please allow scoped applications to read, create, update and " +
                "delete records in these tables.");
        }
        return true;
    };
    /**
     * Synchronize all data for all regions in all accounts.
     */
    SynchronizeAccount.prototype.run = function () {
        // Approach:
        // Check pre-requisites.
        // For every region configured against an account
        //   For every product in that region and every product in every shared portfolio
        //     Insert or update product record
        //     For every portfolio that product is a member of
        //       Insert or update portfolio record
        //       Insert or update product-portfolio association
        //       For every principal attached to that portfolio
        //         Insert or update principal
        //         Insert or update portfolio-principal association.
        // If everything succeeds then delete anything that wasn't updated.
        if (!this.validateInstance()) {
            return false;
        }
        gs.debug("Synchronizing all AWS Service Catalog accounts");
        this._resetPortfolioCache();
        var startTime = new GlideDateTime();
        var overallSuccess = true, totalRequestCount = 0;
        var gr = new GlideRecord('x_126749_aws_sc_account_sync');
        gr.addNotNullQuery('awsaccount');
        gr.query();
        while (gr.next()) {
            var success = true;
            try {
                totalRequestCount += this._ingestAccount(gr.getValue('awsregion'), gr.awsaccount);
            }
            catch (e) {
                var msg = "Error synchronizing AWS Service Catalog account: " +
                    gr.awsaccount.awsname.toString();
                msg += e instanceof Error
                    ? e.name + " " + e.message
                    : e;
                gs.warn(msg);
                success = false;
            }
            overallSuccess = overallSuccess && success;
        }
        // log success/failure.
        if (overallSuccess) {
            gs.debug("Synchronized all AWS Service Catalog data. Deleting all portfolios, products, " +
                "categories, product user criteria, and identities that were not updated since " + startTime);
            this._processRecordsLastUpdatedBefore(startTime);
        }
        else {
            gs.debug("Could not synchronize all AWS Service Catalog data. Skipping delete.");
        }
        var seconds = (new GlideDateTime().getNumericValue() - startTime.getNumericValue()) / 1000.0;
        var result = overallSuccess ? "Successfully synchronized" : "Failed to synchronize";
        gs.info(result + " all AWS Service Catalog accounts in " + seconds + "s");
        gs.debug("Sync job stats: success=" + overallSuccess + ", time=" + seconds + ", #requests=" + totalRequestCount);
    };
    SynchronizeAccount.prototype._ingestAccount = function (region, account) {
        var credential = {
            identity: account.awsaccesskey.toString(),
            secret: account.awssecretaccesskey.getDecryptedValue()
        };
        var serviceCatalog = new AwsServiceCatalog(region, credential);
        var acctName = account.awsname.toString(), acctId = account.sys_id.toString();
        // List all local products, then those that have been shared.
        this._findProductsInPortfolio(acctName, acctId, serviceCatalog, undefined);
        // List all products from shared portfolios
        var shares = serviceCatalog.listAcceptedPortfolioShares().collectAll();
        if (!shares.success) {
            throw new Error("Error loading shared portfolios in " + acctName + ": " + shares.message);
        }
        shares.all.forEach(function (share) {
            this._findProductsInPortfolio(acctName, acctId, serviceCatalog, share['Id']);
        }, this);
        return serviceCatalog.getRequestCount();
    };
    SynchronizeAccount.prototype._findProductsInPortfolio = function (acctName, accountId, serviceCatalog, portfolioId) {
        var products = serviceCatalog.searchProductsAsAdmin({ "PortfolioId": portfolioId }).collectAll();
        if (!products.success) {
            throw new Error("Error loading products in " + acctName + ": " + products.message);
        }
        var relationshipKind = portfolioId ? SynchronizeAccount.portfolioKind.shared : SynchronizeAccount.portfolioKind.local;
        for (var i = 0, l = products.all.length; i < l; i++) {
            var pvs = products.all[i]['ProductViewSummary'];
            var prod = this._ingestProduct(serviceCatalog, accountId, pvs);
            this._associateProductWithAccount(prod, accountId, relationshipKind);
        }
    };
    SynchronizeAccount.prototype._ingestProduct = function (serviceCatalog, accountId, productViewSummary) {
        var productRepo = new ProductRepo(serviceCatalog.region, serviceCatalog), productRecord = productRepo.insertOrUpdate(productViewSummary, this._getProvisioningWorkflow());
        this._ingestProductPortfolios(serviceCatalog, accountId, productRepo, productRecord);
        return productRecord;
    };
    SynchronizeAccount.prototype._ingestProductPortfolios = function (serviceCatalog, accountId, productRepo, product) {
        // Get the local (not shared) portfolios associated with this product.
        var allPortfolios = serviceCatalog.listPortfoliosForProduct(product.awsproductid.toString()).collectAll();
        if (!allPortfolios.success) {
            throw new Error(allPortfolios.message);
        }
        var portfolioCache = this._getPortfolioCache(serviceCatalog.region);
        // For each portfolio:
        //  is it one that's been seen before? Shortcut and use the cached sys_id.
        //  otherwise, insert/update the portfolio and update its principals, then cache its sys_id.
        for (var i = 0; i < allPortfolios.all.length; i++) {
            var portfolio = allPortfolios.all[i];
            if (!portfolioCache[portfolio.Id]) {
                // Not encountered this portfolio during this sync run.
                var portfolioGr = this._updatePortfolio(serviceCatalog, portfolio);
                portfolioCache[portfolio.Id] = portfolioGr.sys_id.toString();
                // Note that the association between accounts and shared portfolios is not tracked.
                // This makes sense in the context of managing products and portfolios: Either the
                // connector also synchronises the origin account and any management of the
                // portfolio and its products should happen through that, or no management of the
                // resources is possible.
                this._associatePortfolioWithAccount(portfolioGr, accountId, SynchronizeAccount.portfolioKind.local);
            }
            productRepo.createPortfolioAssociation(product, portfolioCache[portfolio.Id]);
        }
    };
    SynchronizeAccount.prototype._updatePortfolio = function (serviceCatalog, portfolioDetail) {
        var portfolioRepo = new PortfolioRepo(serviceCatalog.region, serviceCatalog);
        var portfolioGlideRecord = portfolioRepo.insertOrUpdate(portfolioDetail);
        var allPrincipals = serviceCatalog.listPrincipalsForPortfolio(portfolioDetail.Id).collectAll();
        if (!allPrincipals.success) {
            throw new Error(allPrincipals.message);
        }
        if (portfolioGlideRecord.sc_category.nil() && this.createPortfolioSubcategories) {
            portfolioRepo.saveCategoryForPortfolio(portfolioGlideRecord);
        }
        portfolioRepo.savePrincipalsForPortfolio(allPrincipals.all, portfolioGlideRecord);
        return portfolioGlideRecord;
    };
    /**
     * @param region {string} Region in which portfolios are being loaded.
     * @returns {*} An object mapping portfolio IDs to the sys_id of the GlideRecord for that portfolio.
     * @private
     */
    SynchronizeAccount.prototype._getPortfolioCache = function (region) {
        var c = this.portfolioCache[region];
        if (!c) {
            c = this.portfolioCache[region] = {};
        }
        return c;
    };
    SynchronizeAccount.prototype._resetPortfolioCache = function () {
        this.portfolioCache = {};
    };
    SynchronizeAccount.prototype.associateResourceWithAccount = function (table, resource, account, relationship) {
        if (typeof resource === "object") {
            resource = resource.sys_id.toString();
        }
        if (typeof account === "object") {
            account = account.sys_id.toString();
        }
        var gr = new GlideRecord('x_126749_aws_sc_resource_account');
        gr.addQuery('awsaccount', account);
        gr.addQuery('awsresourceid', resource);
        gr.addQuery('awsrelationship', relationship);
        gr.query();
        if (!gr.next()) {
            gr.initialize();
            gr.awsaccount = account;
            gr.awsresource = table;
            gr.awsresourceid = resource;
            gr.awsrelationship = relationship;
            Util.setValue(gr, 'awslastsynctime', new GlideDateTime());
            gr.insert();
        }
        else {
            // ensure the record is always marked as updated, as 'setForceUpdate' is not available to scoped apps
            Util.setValue(gr, 'awslastsynctime', new GlideDateTime());
            gr.update();
        }
        return gr;
    };
    /**
     * Inserts a record into x_126749_aws_sc_resource_account linking product and account
     * if no link already exists.
     *
     * @param product {GlideRecord|String} GlideRecord for or sys_id of a product.
     * @param account {GlideRecord|String} GlideRecord for or sys_id of a account.
     * @param relationship {String} The relationship between the product and the account.
     * @return GlideRecord The GlideRecord for the association.
     */
    SynchronizeAccount.prototype._associateProductWithAccount = function (product, account, relationship) {
        return this.associateResourceWithAccount('x_126749_aws_sc_product', product, account, relationship);
    };
    /**
     * Inserts a record into x_126749_aws_sc_resource_account linking product and account
     * if no link already exists.
     *
     * @param portfolio {GlideRecord|String} GlideRecord for or sys_id of a portfolio.
     * @param account {GlideRecord|String} GlideRecord for or sys_id of a account.
     * @param relationship {String} The relationship between the portfolio and the account.
     * @return GlideRecord The GlideRecord for the association.
     */
    SynchronizeAccount.prototype._associatePortfolioWithAccount = function (portfolio, account, relationship) {
        return this.associateResourceWithAccount('x_126749_aws_sc_portfolio', portfolio, account, relationship);
    };
    /**
     * Delete all Products, Portfolios and Identities that haven't been updated since glideDateTime.
     */
    SynchronizeAccount.prototype._processRecordsLastUpdatedBefore = function (glideDateTime) {
        var productRepo = new ProductRepo("us-east-1", "unused");
        var portfolioRepo = new PortfolioRepo("us-east-1", "unused");
        // Rely on cascade deletion rules for the deletion of unwanted product-portfolio and
        // portfolio-identity associations.
        portfolioRepo.processLastUpdatedBefore(glideDateTime);
        productRepo.processLastUpdatedBefore(glideDateTime);
        this._deleteStaleAccountAssociations(glideDateTime);
        this._deleteOrphanedIdentities();
    };
    SynchronizeAccount.prototype._deleteStaleAccountAssociations = function (dateTime) {
        var portProdAssoc = new GlideRecord('x_126749_aws_sc_resource_account');
        portProdAssoc.addQuery('sys_updated_on', '<', dateTime);
        portProdAssoc.deleteMultiple();
    };
    SynchronizeAccount.prototype._deleteOrphanedIdentities = function () {
        var keep = [];
        // identities referenced by portfolios.
        var idsInUse = new GlideAggregate('x_126749_aws_sc_portfolio_principals');
        idsInUse.groupBy('awsidentity');
        idsInUse.query();
        while (idsInUse.next()) {
            keep.push(idsInUse.awsidentity.toString());
        }
        // identities referenced by provisioned products that are not terminated.
        idsInUse = new GlideAggregate('x_126749_aws_sc_cmdb_ci_pp');
        idsInUse.addQuery('awsproductstatus', '!=', ProvisionedProduct.Status.terminated);
        idsInUse.groupBy('awsidentity');
        idsInUse.query();
        while (idsInUse.next()) {
            keep.push(idsInUse.awsidentity.toString());
        }
        // delete unreferenced records.
        var gr = new GlideRecord('x_126749_aws_sc_aws_identity');
        gr.addQuery('sys_id', 'NOT IN', keep.join(','));
        gr.deleteMultiple();
    };
    SynchronizeAccount.prototype._getProvisioningWorkflow = function () {
        var wf = Util.getWorkflow(C.sysprop.workflow.provision);
        if (!wf) {
            throw new Error("Configuration error, please configure workflow name in system property: " + C.sysprop.workflow.provision);
        }
        return wf.sys_id;
    };
    SynchronizeAccount.portfolioKind = Object.freeze({
        local: 10,
        shared: 20
    });
    return SynchronizeAccount;
}());
]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_include</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>admin</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2017-09-13 15:13:27</sys_created_on><sys_id>935b747fdbc14300a5d3ddd0cf96194a</sys_id><sys_mod_count>63</sys_mod_count><sys_name>SynchronizeAccount</sys_name><sys_package display_value="AWS Service Catalog - 2.0.2" source="x_126749_aws_sc">f0b117a3db32320093a7d7a0cf961912</sys_package><sys_policy>read</sys_policy><sys_scope display_value="AWS Service Catalog - 2.0.2">f0b117a3db32320093a7d7a0cf961912</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_include_935b747fdbc14300a5d3ddd0cf96194a</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>admin</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2019-04-10 14:52:06</sys_updated_on></sys_script_include></record_update>

sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><access>package_private</access><active>true</active><api_name>x_126749_aws_sc.ProductRepo</api_name><client_callable>false</client_callable><description/><name>ProductRepo</name><script><![CDATA[var ProductRepo = /** @class */ (function () {
    function ProductRepo(region, serviceCatalog) {
        this.region = Util.assertExists(region, "region");
        this.serviceCatalog = Util.assertExists(serviceCatalog, "serviceCatalog");
    }
    ProductRepo.prototype.get = function (productId) {
        var gr = new GlideRecord('x_126749_aws_sc_product');
        gr.addQuery('awsproductid', "=", productId);
        gr.addQuery('awsregion', "=", this.region);
        gr.setLimit(1);
        gr.query();
        if (gr.next()) {
            return gr;
        }
        return null;
    };
    ProductRepo.prototype.insertOrUpdate = function (productViewSummary, workflowSysId) {
        var glideRecord = this.get(productViewSummary['ProductId']);
        if (glideRecord) {
            gs.debug("Updating " + productViewSummary['ProductId'] + " " + productViewSummary['Name']);
            this.update(glideRecord, productViewSummary);
        }
        else {
            gs.debug("Inserting " + productViewSummary['ProductId'] + " " + productViewSummary['Name']);
            glideRecord = this.insert(productViewSummary, workflowSysId);
        }
        return glideRecord;
    };
    ProductRepo.prototype.insert = function (productViewSummary, workflowSysId) {
        var gr = new GlideRecord('x_126749_aws_sc_product');
        gs.debug("New product:" + productViewSummary['ProductId']);
        gr.initialize();
        Util.setValue(gr, 'awsproductid', productViewSummary['ProductId']);
        Util.setValue(gr, 'awsregion', this.region);
        this._setProductProperties(gr, productViewSummary);
        // Set category
        var productCategory = ProductRepo.getProductCategory();
        if (productCategory) {
            gr.category = productCategory.sys_id;
        }
        gr.insert();
        // Associate the variable set and user criteria.
        this._attachVariableSet(gr.sys_id, this._getVariableSet().sys_id);
        if (Util.isUserCriteriaEnabled()) {
            var userCriteriaSysId = this._createUserCriteria(gr.sys_id);
            Util.setValue(gr, 'awsusercriteria', userCriteriaSysId);
        }
        Util.setValue(gr, 'workflow', workflowSysId);
        gr.update();
        return gr;
    };
    ProductRepo.prototype.update = function (existingProductGR, productViewSummary) {
        gs.debug("Updating existing record for: " + productViewSummary['ProductId']);
        this._setProductProperties(existingProductGR, productViewSummary);
        existingProductGR.update();
    };
    /**
     * Inserts a record into x_126749_aws_sc_portfolio_products linking product and portfolio
     * if no link already exists, and update last-sync-time if it does.
     *
     * @param product {GlideRecord|String} GlideRecord for or sys_id of a product.
     * @param portfolio {GlideRecord|String} GlideRecord for or sys_id of a portfolio.
     */
    ProductRepo.prototype.createPortfolioAssociation = function (product, portfolio) {
        if (typeof product === "object") {
            product = product.sys_id.toString();
        }
        if (typeof portfolio === "object") {
            portfolio = portfolio.sys_id.toString();
        }
        var pp = new GlideRecord('x_126749_aws_sc_portfolio_products');
        pp.addQuery('awsproduct', product);
        pp.addQuery('awsportfolio', portfolio);
        pp.query();
        if (!pp.next()) {
            pp.initialize();
            pp.awsproduct = product;
            pp.awsportfolio = portfolio;
            Util.setValue(pp, 'awslastsynctime', new GlideDateTime());
            pp.insert();
        }
        else {
            // ensure the record is always marked as updated, as 'setForceUpdate' is not available to scoped apps
            Util.setValue(pp, 'awslastsynctime', new GlideDateTime());
            pp.update();
        }
        if (!pp.awsportfolio.sc_category.nil() &&
            Util.tableActionEnabled("sc_cat_item_category", true, true, true, true)) {
            var catItemCategory = new GlideRecord('sc_cat_item_category');
            catItemCategory.addQuery('sc_cat_item', product);
            catItemCategory.addQuery('sc_category', pp.awsportfolio.sc_category);
            catItemCategory.query();
            if (!catItemCategory.hasNext()) {
                catItemCategory.initialize();
                catItemCategory.sc_cat_item = product;
                catItemCategory.sc_category = pp.awsportfolio.sc_category;
                catItemCategory.insert();
            }
        }
    };
    ProductRepo.prototype.processLastUpdatedBefore = function (glideDateTime) {
        this._deleteOlderThan(glideDateTime);
    };
    ProductRepo.getProductCategory = function () {
        var categoryProperty = gs.getProperty('x_126749_aws_sc.product_category_name');
        if (categoryProperty) {
            var gr = new GlideRecord('sc_category');
            if (gr.get(categoryProperty) || gr.get('title', categoryProperty)) {
                return gr;
            }
        }
        return null;
    };
    ProductRepo.prototype._deleteOlderThan = function (glideDateTime) {
        var deleteUserCriteria = Util.isUserCriteriaEnabled();
        if (deleteUserCriteria) {
            gs.debug("Deleting products, portfolio associations and user criteria older than " + glideDateTime);
        }
        else {
            gs.debug("Deleting products and portfolio associations older than " + glideDateTime);
        }
        var prod = new GlideRecord('x_126749_aws_sc_product');
        prod.addQuery('sys_updated_on', '<', glideDateTime);
        prod.query();
        var productsToDelete = [];
        var criteriaToDelete = [];
        while (prod.next()) {
            productsToDelete.push(prod.sys_id.toString());
            if (deleteUserCriteria && !prod.awsusercriteria.nil()) {
                criteriaToDelete.push(prod.awsusercriteria.toString());
            }
        }
        gs.debug("Products to delete: " + productsToDelete.join(','));
        var products = new GlideRecord('x_126749_aws_sc_product');
        products.addQuery('sys_id', 'IN', productsToDelete.join(','));
        products.deleteMultiple();
        if (deleteUserCriteria) {
            for (var i = 0; i < criteriaToDelete.length; i++) {
                var ucapi = new sn_uc.UserCriteria(criteriaToDelete[i]);
                ucapi.deleteRecord();
            }
        }
        // delete associations that have not been updated as these must have been
        // removed from the portfolio within AWS Service Catalog since last sync
        var portProdAssoc = new GlideRecord('x_126749_aws_sc_portfolio_products');
        portProdAssoc.addQuery('sys_updated_on', '<', glideDateTime);
        portProdAssoc.deleteMultiple();
    };
    ProductRepo.prototype._setProductProperties = function (gr, productViewSummary) {
        Util.setValue(gr, 'awsid', productViewSummary['Id']);
        Util.setValue(gr, "name", productViewSummary['Name']); // from sc_cat_item
        Util.setValue(gr, 'awsowner', productViewSummary['Owner']);
        Util.setValue(gr, 'awsdistributor', productViewSummary['Distributor']);
        Util.setValue(gr, 'awstype', productViewSummary['Type']);
        Util.setValue(gr, 'awshasdefaultpath', productViewSummary['HasDefaultPath']);
        Util.setValue(gr, 'awssupportdescription', productViewSummary['SupportDescription']);
        Util.setValue(gr, 'awssupportemail', productViewSummary['SupportEmail']);
        Util.setValue(gr, 'awssupporturl', productViewSummary['SupportUrl']);
        // Descriptions are from sc_cat_item
        var awsDescription = productViewSummary['ShortDescription'];
        Util.setValue(gr, "short_description", this._getShortDescription(awsDescription));
        Util.setValue(gr, "description", awsDescription);
        // ensure the record is always marked as updated, as 'setForceUpdate' is not available to scoped apps
        Util.setValue(gr, 'awslastsynctime', new GlideDateTime());
    };
    ProductRepo.prototype._getVariableSet = function () {
        var gr = new GlideRecord('item_option_new_set');
        // Could obtain this from a system property.
        if (gr.get('name', 'AWS Service Catalog Variables')) {
            return gr;
        }
        return null;
    };
    ProductRepo.prototype._attachVariableSet = function (catalogItemId, variableSetId) {
        var m2m = new sn_sc.CatalogItemVariableSetM2M();
        m2m.setAttributes({ "sc_cat_item": catalogItemId, "variable_set": variableSetId });
        m2m.create(true);
    };
    /**
     * Create a user criteria to control access to this product.
     * @private
     */
    ProductRepo.prototype._createUserCriteria = function (productSysId) {
        // Create the user criteria
        var uc = new sn_uc.UserCriteria();
        uc.setName('Controls access to AWS Service Catalog product: ' + productSysId);
        uc.setAdvanced(true);
        uc.setScript(ProductUserCriteria.create(productSysId));
        var ucSysId = uc.create();
        // And associate it with the product.
        var link = new GlideRecord('sc_cat_item_user_criteria_mtom');
        link.initialize();
        link.sc_cat_item = productSysId;
        link.user_criteria = ucSysId;
        link.insert();
        return ucSysId;
    };
    ProductRepo.prototype._getShortDescription = function (text) {
        // In theory should not be required as short description is mandatory, but coding defensively
        if (!text) {
            return null;
        }
        // You can't use Java's reserved words for variable names in ServiceNow.
        var overview = text;
        if (text.length > 200) {
            // find the last whitespace in the first 196 characters and replace
            // the three characters after it with "..."
            var idx = 197;
            do {
                if (text.charAt(idx - 1).match(/\s/)) {
                    break;
                }
            } while (--idx > 0);
            if (idx <= 0) {
                // just truncate the string if it's 200 characters without whitespace!
                idx = 197;
            }
            overview = text.substring(0, idx) + "...";
        }
        return overview;
    };
    return ProductRepo;
}());
ProductRepo.prototype.type = "ProductRepo";
]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_include</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>admin</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2017-09-12 08:20:26</sys_created_on><sys_id>4e33d2d7db010300cb04d421cf961940</sys_id><sys_mod_count>64</sys_mod_count><sys_name>ProductRepo</sys_name><sys_package display_value="AWS Service Catalog - 2.0.2" source="x_126749_aws_sc">f0b117a3db32320093a7d7a0cf961912</sys_package><sys_policy>read</sys_policy><sys_scope display_value="AWS Service Catalog - 2.0.2">f0b117a3db32320093a7d7a0cf961912</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_include_4e33d2d7db010300cb04d421cf961940</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>admin</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2019-04-09 16:36:29</sys_updated_on></sys_script_include></record_update>

sys_update_xml.name: sys_ui_page_6965f5cfdb6b13002dc6f6fdbf961922
sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_ui_page"><sys_ui_page action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><category>general</category><client_script/><description>A page to update a product provisioned through Service Catalog</description><direct>false</direct><endpoint>x_126749_aws_sc_update_product.do</endpoint><html><![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?>
<j:jelly trim="false" xmlns:j="jelly:core" xmlns:g="glide" xmlns:j2="null" xmlns:g2="null">
  <g:requires name="angular_includes_1.4.jsx" />
  <g:requires name="x_126749_aws_sc.awsComponents.jsdbx"/>
  <g:requires name="x_126749_aws_sc.productCatalog.jsdbx"/>
  <head>
    <title>Update Provisioned Product</title>
  </head>
  <body ng-app="productCatalog">

  <g:evaluate object="true">
      // Get session token. Required so we can use $http in Service Portal. See
      // https://community.servicenow.com/community?id=community_blog&sys_id=bebc6e25dbd0dbc01dcaf3231f961928
      // Note ServiceNow documentation says that GlideSystem's getSessionToken()
      // method "is no longer available. Instead, use gs.getSession().getSessionToken()."
      // Experimentally on Istanbul this is not true on this page, only in server scripts.
      var session = gs.getSession();
      var token;
      gs.info('session found ' + session);
      var token = session.getSessionToken();
      if (!token) {
          try {
              token = gs.getSessionToken();
          } catch (err) {
              gs.debug('Fallback to GlideSession.getSessionToken failed');
          }
      }
  </g:evaluate>

  <header></header>
  <main>
      <update-product-ui user-token="$[token]"></update-product-ui>
  </main>
  <footer></footer>
  </body>
</j:jelly>
]]></html><name>update_product</name><processing_script/><sys_class_name>sys_ui_page</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>admin</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2018-07-31 14:22:02</sys_created_on><sys_id>6965f5cfdb6b13002dc6f6fdbf961922</sys_id><sys_mod_count>7</sys_mod_count><sys_name>update_product</sys_name><sys_package display_value="AWS Service Catalog - 2.0.2" source="x_126749_aws_sc">f0b117a3db32320093a7d7a0cf961912</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="AWS Service Catalog - 2.0.2">f0b117a3db32320093a7d7a0cf961912</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_ui_page_6965f5cfdb6b13002dc6f6fdbf961922</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>admin</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2018-08-15 15:47:11</sys_updated_on></sys_ui_page></record_update>

provisionedProduct.executePlan(c.productSysId) : provisionedProduct.updateProvisionedProduct(c.productSysId, c.model.launchOption, c.model.productVersion, c.model.params, options); promise.then(function(result) { if (!result.success) { spUtil.addErrorMessage(result.message ? result.message : 'failed to update product'); c.updateRequested = false; return; } spUtil.addInfoMessage('Update requested'); var productPage = 'id=aws_sc_pp_details&sys_id=' + c.productSysId; $location.search(productPage); c.inputsDisabled = true; c.updateRequested = false; }, function(err) { c.recordError(err); c.inputsDisabled = false; c.updateRequested = false; }); }; c.initialize(); $scope.$watch('c.data.sessionToken', c.setUserToken); } ]]>c.form-group { margin-bottom: 10px; } .bs-callout { margin: 10px 0 !important; padding: 20px !important; border-left-style: solid; border-left-width: 10px; } .bs-callout-error { background-color: #fdf7f7; border-color: #d9534f; } .bs-callout-ok { background-color: #f4f8fa; border-color: #5bc0de; } .label.event { float: right; } .panel-body > div { margin-bottom: 15px; } fa { margin-right: 10px; } .intro { padding: 20px !important } .arn { margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; } .glyphicon-exclamation-sign { color: #d9534f; } .timeline-heading a { cursor: pointer; } sp_instanceWidget to render a form for updating a provisioned producttrueaws-sc-update-formfalseAWS SC Service Portal Update Formfalsefalsesp_widgetadmin2018-08-03 12:48:0549acf004db7793002dc6f6fdbf96193277AWS SC Service Portal Update Formf0b117a3db32320093a7d7a0cf961912f0b117a3db32320093a7d7a0cf961912sp_widget_49acf004db7793002dc6f6fdbf961932admin2019-04-10 14:07:22

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><access>package_private</access><active>true</active><api_name>x_126749_aws_sc.PortfolioRepo</api_name><client_callable>false</client_callable><description/><name>PortfolioRepo</name><script><![CDATA[var PortfolioRepo = /** @class */ (function () {
    function PortfolioRepo(region, serviceCatalog) {
        this.region = Util.assertExists(region, "region");
        this.serviceCatalog = Util.assertExists(serviceCatalog, "serviceCatalog");
    }
    PortfolioRepo.prototype.get = function (portFolioId) {
        var gr = new GlideRecord('x_126749_aws_sc_portfolio');
        gr.addQuery('awsid', "=", portFolioId);
        gr.addQuery('awsregion', "=", this.region);
        gr.setLimit(1);
        gr.query();
        if (gr.next()) {
            return gr;
        }
        return null;
    };
    PortfolioRepo.prototype.insertOrUpdate = function (portfolioDetail) {
        var glideRecord = this.get(portfolioDetail['Id']);
        if (glideRecord) {
            this._updatePortfolio(glideRecord, portfolioDetail);
        }
        else {
            glideRecord = this._insertPortfolio(portfolioDetail);
        }
        return glideRecord;
    };
    PortfolioRepo.prototype._insertPortfolio = function (portfolioDetail) {
        var gr = new GlideRecord('x_126749_aws_sc_portfolio');
        gr.initialize();
        Util.setValue(gr, 'awsid', portfolioDetail["Id"]);
        Util.setValue(gr, 'awsregion', this.region);
        this._setPortfolioProperties(gr, portfolioDetail);
        gr.insert();
        return gr;
    };
    PortfolioRepo.prototype._updatePortfolio = function (existingGlideRecord, portfolioDetail) {
        this._setPortfolioProperties(existingGlideRecord, portfolioDetail);
        existingGlideRecord.update();
    };
    PortfolioRepo.prototype.processLastUpdatedBefore = function (glideDateTime) {
        this._deletePortfoliosOlderThan(glideDateTime);
    };
    PortfolioRepo.prototype._deletePortfoliosOlderThan = function (glideDateTime) {
        gs.debug("Deleting any portfolios older than " + glideDateTime);
        var portfolioGR = new GlideRecord('x_126749_aws_sc_portfolio');
        var categoriesToDelete = [];
        portfolioGR.addQuery('sys_updated_on', '<', glideDateTime);
        portfolioGR.query();
        while (portfolioGR.next()) {
            categoriesToDelete.push(portfolioGR.sc_category.toString());
        }
        portfolioGR.deleteMultiple();
        var categoryGR = new GlideRecord('sc_category');
        categoryGR.addQuery('sys_id', 'IN', categoriesToDelete.join(','));
        categoryGR.deleteMultiple();
    };
    PortfolioRepo.prototype.getPrincipalsForPortfolio = function (portfolioGR) {
        var principals = [];
        var pp = new GlideRecord('x_126749_aws_sc_portfolio_principals');
        pp.addQuery('awsportfolio', portfolioGR.sys_id);
        pp.query();
        while (pp.next()) {
            principals.push({ PrincipalARN: pp.awsidentity.awsarn.toString() });
        }
        return principals;
    };
    PortfolioRepo.prototype.savePrincipalsForPortfolio = function (principals, portfolioGR) {
        // The set of principals already stored.
        var outdated = this.getPrincipalsForPortfolio(portfolioGR);
        // Ignore principals the connector already knows about.
        for (var i = 0; i < principals.length; i++) {
            var principal = principals[i];
            for (var j = 0; j < outdated.length; j++) {
                var existing = outdated[j];
                if (existing && principal['PrincipalARN'] === existing['PrincipalARN']) {
                    delete principals[i];
                    delete outdated[j];
                    break;
                }
            }
        }
        // principals -> new principals to associate
        // outdated   -> outdated associations to delete
        this._addPrincipalsForPortfolio(principals, portfolioGR);
        this._deletePrincipalsFromPortfolio(outdated, portfolioGR);
    };
    PortfolioRepo.prototype.saveCategoryForPortfolio = function (portfolioGR) {
        var parentCategory = ProductRepo.getProductCategory();
        if (!parentCategory) {
            return null;
        }
        var cat = new GlideRecord('sc_category');
        cat.addQuery('parent', parentCategory.sys_id);
        cat.addQuery('title', portfolioGR.awsdisplayname);
        cat.setLimit(1);
        cat.query();
        if (!cat.next()) {
            cat.initialize();
            cat.title = portfolioGR.awsdisplayname;
            cat.description = portfolioGR.awsdescription;
            cat.sys_name = portfolioGR.awsdisplayname;
            cat.parent = parentCategory.sys_id;
            cat.insert();
            // Copy the parent category's icon to the new category.
            var gsa = new GlideSysAttachment();
            gsa.copy('sc_category', parentCategory.sys_id, 'sc_category', cat.sys_id);
        }
        portfolioGR.sc_category = cat.sys_id;
        portfolioGR.update();
        return cat;
    };
    PortfolioRepo.prototype._addPrincipalsForPortfolio = function (principals, portfolioGR) {
        for (var i = 0; i < principals.length; i++) {
            if (principals[i]) {
                this._addPrincipalForPortfolio(principals[i], portfolioGR);
            }
        }
    };
    PortfolioRepo.prototype._getOrCreateAwsIdentityForPrincipal = function (principal) {
        var arn = principal['PrincipalARN'];
        var awsid = new GlideRecord('x_126749_aws_sc_aws_identity');
        if (!awsid.get('awsarn', arn)) {
            awsid.initialize();
            Util.setValue(awsid, 'awsarn', arn);
            awsid.insert();
        }
        return awsid;
    };
    PortfolioRepo.prototype._addPrincipalForPortfolio = function (principal, portfolioGR) {
        var awsid = this._getOrCreateAwsIdentityForPrincipal(principal);
        var pp = new GlideRecord('x_126749_aws_sc_portfolio_principals');
        pp.addQuery('awsportfolio', portfolioGR.sys_id);
        pp.addQuery('awsidentity', awsid.sys_id);
        pp.query();
        if (!pp.next()) {
            pp.initialize();
            Util.setValue(pp, 'awsportfolio', portfolioGR.sys_id);
            Util.setValue(pp, 'awsidentity', awsid.sys_id);
            pp.insert();
        }
    };
    PortfolioRepo.prototype._deletePrincipalFromPortfolio = function (principal, portfolioGR) {
        var awsid = this._getOrCreateAwsIdentityForPrincipal(principal);
        var pp = new GlideRecord('x_126749_aws_sc_portfolio_principals');
        pp.addQuery('awsportfolio', portfolioGR.sys_id);
        pp.addQuery('awsidentity', awsid.sys_id);
        pp.deleteMultiple();
    };
    PortfolioRepo.prototype._deletePrincipalsFromPortfolio = function (principals, portfolioGR) {
        for (var i = 0; i < principals.length; i++) {
            if (principals[i]) {
                this._deletePrincipalFromPortfolio(principals[i], portfolioGR);
            }
        }
    };
    PortfolioRepo.prototype._setPortfolioProperties = function (gr, portfolioDetail) {
        Util.setValue(gr, 'awsarn', portfolioDetail['ARN']);
        Util.setValue(gr, 'awscreatedtime', Util.toGlideDateTime(portfolioDetail['CreatedTime']));
        Util.setValue(gr, 'awsdescription', portfolioDetail['Description']);
        Util.setValue(gr, 'awsdisplayname', portfolioDetail['DisplayName']);
        Util.setValue(gr, 'awsprovidername', portfolioDetail['ProviderName']);
        // ensure the record is always marked as updated, as 'setForceUpdate' is not available to scoped apps
        Util.setValue(gr, 'awslastsynctime', new GlideDateTime());
    };
    return PortfolioRepo;
}());
PortfolioRepo.prototype.type = "PortfolioRepo";

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update sys_domain="global" table="sys_script"><sys_script action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><abort_action>false</abort_action><access>package_private</access><action_delete>true</action_delete><action_insert>false</action_insert><action_query>false</action_query><action_update>false</action_update><active>true</active><add_message>false</add_message><advanced>true</advanced><change_fields>false</change_fields><client_callable>false</client_callable><collection>x_126749_aws_sc_portfolio_products</collection><condition/><description/><execute_function>false</execute_function><filter_condition/><is_rest>false</is_rest><message/><name>Delete Category and Product relationship</name><order>100</order><priority>100</priority><rest_method/><rest_method_text/><rest_service/><rest_service_text/><rest_variables/><role_conditions/><script><![CDATA[/**
 * Disassociate the Service Catalog category (sc_category table) corresponding to the portfolio (current) to the product (x_126749_aws_sc_product table)
 * @param current Portfolio record from x_126749_aws_sc_portfolio_products table
 * @param previous Portfolio record from x_126749_aws_sc_portfolio_products table
 */
(function executeRule(current, previous /*null when async*/) {
    var gr = new GlideRecord('sc_cat_item_category');
    gr.addQuery('sc_cat_item', '=', current.awsproduct);
    gr.addQuery('sc_category', '=', current.awsportfolio.sc_category);
    gr.deleteMultiple();
})(current, previous);
]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>admin</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2019-03-14 14:29:17</sys_created_on><sys_domain>global</sys_domain><sys_domain_path>/</sys_domain_path><sys_id>5bdea1374f8033001a959acf9310c70b</sys_id><sys_mod_count>8</sys_mod_count><sys_name>Delete Category and Product relationship</sys_name><sys_overrides/><sys_package display_value="AWS Service Catalog - 2.0.2" source="x_126749_aws_sc">f0b117a3db32320093a7d7a0cf961912</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="AWS Service Catalog - 2.0.2">f0b117a3db32320093a7d7a0cf961912</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_5bdea1374f8033001a959acf9310c70b</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>admin</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2019-04-04 11:36:05</sys_updated_on><template/><when>before</when></sys_script><sys_translated_text action="delete_multiple" query="documentkey=5bdea1374f8033001a959acf9310c70b"/></record_update>
